       return;\n       }\n       cacheResult(stdout);\n     });\n     ```\n\n2. **Hardcoded Live API Credential**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:20`\n   - Severity (initial): Critical\n   - OWASP category: A07 Identification and Authentication Failures\n   - Description: A live API token (`sk_live_...`) is hardcoded at module scope. Any actor with read access to the repository (or its git history) obtains the token. It cannot be rotated without a code change and a history rewrite, and it remains exposed indefinitely in git history even after removal.\n   - Code context:\n     ```ts\n     // review-src/disk-info.ts:20\n     const API_TOKEN = 'sk_live_8f3a2b9c10d44e7fa1b6c2e9d0447aa1';\n     ```\n\n3. **Path Traversal into fsSize**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:46`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP category: A01 Broken Access Control\n   - Description: The same unvalidated `path` from `query.mountPath` is passed directly to `fsSize(path)`. An attacker can supply `../../etc/shadow` or any absolute path to read filesystem metadata outside the intended mount scope. No path canonicalisation, prefix check, or allow-list guards this sink.\n   - Code context:\n     ```ts\n     // review-src/disk-info.ts:46-48\n     const size = await fsSize(path);\n     return { path, size };\n     ```\n\n4. **Plaintext Secret Transmission + Second Injection**\n   - File: `review-src/disk-info.ts:68-69`\n   - Severity (initial): Important\n   - OWASP category: A02 Cryptographic Failures / A03 Injection\n   - Description: `writeCache` constructs an `http://` URL embedding `API_TOKEN` as a query parameter, then passes it to `exec('curl ...')`. Two issues compound: (a) the credential travels over unencrypted HTTP and will appear in server access logs, network captures, and the shell history of any process that inherits the environment; (b) `JSON.stringify(parsed)` is injected into the curl `-d` argument inside single quotes without escaping -- a single-quote character